=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: From the corresponding methoxy-substituted naphthol bearing the required benzenoid substitution pattern, perform regioselective Friedel-Crafts propionylation (e.g. CH3CH2COCl/AlCl3) to give the propionyl-substituted methoxy naphthol. | Step 2: Reduce/deoxygenate that aryl ketone to the straight-chain n-propyl group (e.g. Wolff-Kishner, Clemmensen, or reduction then hydrogenolysis) to obtain the methoxy/n-propyl-substituted naphthol. | Step 3: Formylate ortho to the phenolic OH (e.g. Vilsmeier-Haack or Duff formylation) to give the key methoxy/n-propyl-substituted ortho-hydroxynaphthaldehyde. | Step 4: Condense this ortho-hydroxynaphthaldehyde with diethyl malonate under Knoevenagel conditions, then cyclize/lactonize to furnish the fused coumarin-3-carboxylate target, CCCc1c(OC)ccc2cc(C(=O)OCC)c(=O)oc12.

